Subject: SOP Color Channel Vocabulary Realization

Description: SOP-HG event record for defining semantic color channels for SOP optical and holographic work.

@ [source] F:\.sop\platform\SOPColorChannelVocabulary.sop
@ [source] F:\.sop\platform\SOPOpticalChain.sop
@ [source] F:\.sop\platform\HolographicSOPScaffold.sop

& [Graph:2026-06-24_sop_color_channel_vocabulary_050] is a SOP-HG graph
  + [N:event:2026-06-24_sop_color_channel_vocabulary_050] is SOP color channel vocabulary realization
    = role: direct_focus_continuation
  + [N:vocabulary:sop_color_channel_vocabulary] is channel language for semantic optics over SOP
  + [N:set:required_minimum] is source, focus, boundary, outside, and output channels
  + [N:set:proof_sensitive] is evidence, claim, honesty, and trace channels
  + [N:set:risk_sensitive] is caution, security, boundary, and outside channels
  + [N:set:meaning_navigation] is periphery, relation, weight, and wisdom channels
  + [N:outside:channel_boundary] is unnamed, unsupported, untraced, or unbounded signal color

  / [E:defines:sop_color_channel_vocabulary_050] -(defines; event=N:event:2026-06-24_sop_color_channel_vocabulary_050; vocabulary=N:vocabulary:sop_color_channel_vocabulary; minimum=N:set:required_minimum)> [Graph:2026-06-24_sop_color_channel_vocabulary_050]
    = realization: SOP optical work now has explicit channels for signal organization
  / [E:guards:proof_and_risk_channels_050] -(guards; vocabulary=N:vocabulary:sop_color_channel_vocabulary; proof=N:set:proof_sensitive; risk=N:set:risk_sensitive)> [Graph:2026-06-24_sop_color_channel_vocabulary_050]
    = realization: color channels cannot raise proof status without evidence, trace, honesty, and caution
  / [E:bounds:channel_boundary_050] -(bounds; vocabulary=N:vocabulary:sop_color_channel_vocabulary; outside=N:outside:channel_boundary)> [Graph:2026-06-24_sop_color_channel_vocabulary_050]
    = caution: unnamed or unsupported signal colors remain outside

  = inside: SOPColorChannelVocabulary.sop, required channels, proof-sensitive channels, risk-sensitive channels, meaning-navigation channels
  = boundary: symbolic semantic color channels for SOP work; not hidden activation color or physical light
  = outside: unnamed channels, unsupported proof, hidden activations, and physical optics
